def: Tending to prohibit, forbid, or exclude; implying prohibition;forbidding; as, a prohibitory law; a prohibitory price. Prohibitoryindex. (R. C. Ch.) See under Index.
To take; to steal; to filch. [Obs.]This canon it in his hand nam. Chaucer.
A crystalline hydrocarbon derivative, metameric with orcin, butproduced artificially; -- called also cresorcin.
Of or related to protein; albuminous; proteid.
Of or pertaining to the time of Allhallows. [Obs.] "Allhallownsummer." Shak. (i. e., late summer; "Indian Summer").
Ill governed, as a people; ill directed. "Rude, misgovernedhands." Shak.
Pertaining to, or derived from, the Bible; as, biblicallearning; biblical authority.
A sharpened flint for the lock of a gun, to ignite the charge.It was in common use before the introduction of percussion caps.

A rare element of the carbon-silicon group, intermediatebetween the metals and nonmetals, obtained from the mineral zircon asa dark sooty powder, or as a gray metallic crystalline substance.Symbol Zr. Atomic weight, 90.4.
